			<ns0:name>elijahtaylor@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/elijahtaylor@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">In attempting to get Mono to self host, I ran into several limitations of the file system access sel_ldr exposes with its -a option.

Here is a list of functions that would be good to support through -a for Mono specifically, but probably other systems that want to self host part of their build/install.  It is sorted by difficulty of workaround (most difficult to workaround listed first) in the mono project:

ftruncate
mkdir
getcwd
